body_html: All I can think of is after apt-get purge command you may need to manually remove libprotobuf files under /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/, if they are still there. Then install the correct protobuf version using pip as described in tensorflow.org.

body: All I can think of is after apt-get purge command you may need to manually remove libprotobuf files under  `/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/`, if they are still there. Then install the correct protobuf version using `pip` as described in tensorflow.org.
